Class DaysForClasses

All Implemented Interfaces:
java.io.Serializable, java.lang.Comparable<DaysForClasses>
public class DaysForClasses
extends SchedulePreference
implements java.lang.Comparable<DaysForClasses>, java.io.Serializable

Represents the schedule preference which specifies which days of the week courses should be scheduled (MWF, TR, etc.). Day abbreviations are as follows: SUN - Su MON - M TUE - T WED - W THU - R FRI - F SAT - Sa

Author:
Eric Liebowitz

Conveniently-defined preference for teaching a class any/all five days of the work week. Probably most useful as a default DaysForClasses preference.

DaysForClasses

public DaysForClasses(java.lang.String name,
                      int weight,
                      int[] days)
Builds a preference for which days to offer courses.

Parameters:
name - The name this preference will be referred to as
weight - The priority (0 - 10...10 is non-violatable)
days - An array of integers representing days of the week. (Sun = 0, 6 = Sat). This array will be used to create the "Week" object.
